It was not immediately known who was behind the incident, a police spokesperson said. Denmark has been a vocal critic of Russia alongside other Western nations following last year’s invasion of Ukraine. The 110-year-old bronze statue depicts the little mermaid from 19th-century Danish author Hans Christian Andersen’s tale of the same name, and is sat on a rock by a waterside promenade. The white, blue and red stripes of the Russian flag were painted across the front of the stone. (Reporting by Louise Breusch Rasmussen, Johannes Gotfredsen-Birkebaek, Editing by Terje Solsvik and Raissa Kasolowsky)